          "title": "JSDoc misattributes awaiting_user to chat actions",
          "body": "Line 12 says awaiting_user, user_acted, user_deferred are all written by 'chat actions'. In production source, chat-actions.ts only writes user_deferred (line 187) and user_acted (line 217). awaiting_user is written by orchestrators \u2014 runs-repo.test.ts line 222 names it 'orchestrator-spawned awaiting_user' and the value never appears in chat-actions.ts source. The comment groups all three under one writer which is wrong: awaiting_user belongs under orchestrators, not chat actions. Fix: split the list \u2014 'awaiting_user (orchestrators), user_acted + user_deferred (chat actions)'.",
